# Desktop alpha releases

For the full checklist, read and follow
[`.agents/skills/cutlass-release/SKILL.md`](../../.agents/skills/cutlass-release/SKILL.md).
Do **not** invent a different ship path.

## Hard gates

- Ship **only** on an explicit user ask to release / publish / cut an alpha.
- **Never tag from `macos-dev`.** Tag only the merge tip of `main` after a
  green PR merge.
- Bump `[workspace.package].version` in root `Cargo.toml` **past** the last
  shipped Cargo version before tagging (reusing a shipped version reuses asset
  names and confuses the Release).
- Keep versions in sync: `Cargo.toml` / `Cargo.lock`,
  `packaging/macos/Info.plist` (`CFBundleShortVersionString` /
  `CFBundleVersion`), and examples in `packaging/README.md`.
- Rewrite `CHANGELOG.md` for **this** release only ā€” the Release workflow
  uploads the whole file as the GitHub Release body.
- CI clippy is `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings`. Fix
  locally before opening / merging the release PR.
- Desktop tags: `alpha-X.Y.Z`. Python / PyPI is a **separate** `py-v*` track ā€”
  do not mix them into a desktop release unless asked.

## Out of scope unless asked

Notarization, DMG, Intel macOS, Authenticode, `cutlass-py` PyPI publish.
